author: Kim Brunhuber
title: 'Eerily quiet': How California's early action against COVID-19 delayed the surge at hospitals
description: Since the pandemic began, California hospitals have been preparing for an influx of COVID-19 patients — the dreaded surge. It has yet to arrive. Evidence is mounting that the state's early action — including the first statewide stay-at-home order in the U.S. …
